Package: SuperSurv
Type: Package
Title: Unified Machine Learning Ensembles and Interpretability for Survival Data
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: 
    person("Yue", "Lyu", email = "yuelyu0521@gmail.com", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: Implements a Double Super Learner framework for right-censored survival data. The package fits convex combinations of parametric, semiparametric, and machine-learning base learners by minimizing cross-validated risk with inverse probability of censoring weighting (IPCW). Includes high-dimensional variable screening methods, automated hyperparameter grid search, and prediction performance evaluation (e.g., Brier score, Uno’s C-index, time-dependent AUC). Provides global and local interpretability tools for survival ensembles, including SHAP-based explanations.
